This paper is primarily focused on network protocols and their performance, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of deep learning for congestion control identification suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) as well. Additionally, the paper discusses security implications of identifying congestion control variants in encrypted traffic, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of packet arrival data also suggests a potential focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT) in terms of analyzing network traffic.
